.%20Air%20Force%20F-15E%20Strike%20Eagle%20aircraft%20prepares%20to%20land%20at%20a%20base%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20Jan.%2018%2C%202026.%20The%20F-15E%20Strike%20Eagle%20is%20a%20dual-role%20fighter%20designed%20to%20perform%20air-to-air%20and%20air-to-ground%20missions%20at%20low%20altitude%2C%20day%20or%20night%20and%20in%20all%20weather.%3Cp%3EU.S.%20Air%20Force%20photo%20by%20Senior%20Airman%20Jonah%20Bliss%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20US%20Air%20Force%20deployed%20F-15E%20Strike%20Eagles%20during%20Operation%20Epic%20Fury%20against%20Iran.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20fighter%20jets%20are%20designed%20for%20air-to-air%20and%20air-to-ground%20combat%20in%20all%20weather%2C%20day%20or%20night.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EKuwait%20mistakenly%20shot%20down%20three%20F-15E%20Strike%20Eagles%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Bfriendly%20fire%26quot%3B%20incident%2C%20CENTCOM%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fair-force-f-15es-new-electronic-warfare-hard-to-kill-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EF-15E%20Strike%20Eagles%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20fighter%20jets%20designed%20for%20air-to-air%20and%20air-to-ground%20combat%2C%20are%20usually%20a%20dominating%20force%20in%20the%20skies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20three%20F-15E%20Strike%20Eagles%20were%20mistakenly%20shot%20down%20by%20Kuwait%20during%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-weapons-used-to-attack-iran-fend-off-retaliation-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EOperation%20Epic%20Fury%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20brought%20renewed%20attention%20to%20one%20of%20the%20Air%20Force's%20fastest%2C%20most%20versatile%20aircraft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20a%20closer%20look%20at%20the%20F-15E%20Strike%20Eagle%2C%20an%20advanced%20aircraft%20the%20US%20is%20using%20to%20destroy%20Iran's%20missile%20arsenal%20and%20drone%20bases%20from%20the%20skies%20above%20Iran.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20F-15E%20Strike%20Eagle%20has%20been%20in%20service%20in%20the%20US%20Air%20Force%20for%20nearly%2040%20years.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223162%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20F-15E%20Strike%20Eagle.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b1ae5ba7a4f9df67ba2b26%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222104%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20F-15E%20Strike%20Eagle%2C%20aircraft%20assigned%20to%20the%2040th%20Flight%20Test%20Squadron%2C%20Eglin%20Air%20Force%20Base%2C%20Florida%2C%20takes%20off%20from%20Nellis%20AFB%2C%20Nevada%2C%20Feb.%2020%2C%202026.%20The%2040th%20FLTS%20conducts%20developmental%20flight%20tests%20for%20fighter%20aircraft%2C%20focusing%20on%20weapon%20systems%2C%20software%20upgrades%2C%20and%20avionics.%3Cp%3EU.S.%20Air%20Force%20photo%20by%20Airman%201st%20Class%20Jasmine%20Thomas%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20F-15A%20model%20flew%20in%201972%2C%20and%20the%20first%20F-15Es%20were%20produced%20in%201988%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.af.mil%2FAbout-Us%2FFact-Sheets%2FDisplay%2FArticle%2F104499%2Ff-15e-strike-eagle%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20Air%20Force%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EIt's%20the%20fastest%20crewed%20aircraft%20in%20the%20US%20Air%20Force.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225807%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20F-15E%20Strike%20Eagle%20flies%20through%20the%20sky.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b1b16da7a4f9df67ba2b95%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223690%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20U.S.%20Air%20Force%20F-15E%20Strike%20Eagle%20assigned%20to%20the%2048th%20Fighter%20Wing%20flies%20during%20Exercise%20Ocean%20Sky%2025%20at%20Gando%20Air%20Base%2C%20Gran%20Canaria%2C%20Spain%2C%20Oct.%2020%2C%202025.%20This%20annual%20exercise%20is%20designed%20to%20increase%20the%20operational%20proficiency%20of%20pilots%2C%20aircrew%20and%20air%20defense%20personnel%20through%20realistic%2C%20high-tempo%20air-to-air%20missions%2C%20supporting%20continued%20efforts%20to%20strengthen%20partnerships%2C%20alliances%20and%20combat%20readiness.%3Cp%3EU.S.%20Air%20Force%20photo%20by%20Staff%20Sgt.%20Elizabeth%20Davis%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20air-to-air%20and%20air-to-ground%20attack%20aircraft%20can%20fly%20at%201%2C875%20miles%20per%20hour%2C%20or%202.5%20times%20the%20speed%20of%20sound.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20F-15E%20Strike%20Eagle's%20high%20thrust-to-weight%20ratio%20enables%20it%20to%20accelerate%20during%20vertical%20climb.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223371%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20F-15E%20Strike%20Eagle.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b1af35a96e437d6eb82493%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222247%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20U.S.%20Air%20Force%20F-15E%20Strike%20Eagle%20turns%20left%20in%20the%20air%20during%20exercise%20Marauder%20Shield%2026.1%20within%20the%20U.S.%20Central%20Command%20area%20of%20responsibility%2C%20Nov.%2011%2C%202025.%20Marauder%20Shield%2026.1%20was%20focused%20on%20enhancing%20counter-Unmanned%20Aircraft%20Systems%20capabilities%2C%20fighter%20integration%2C%20improving%20command%20and%20control%2C%20and%20fostering%20closer%20cooperation%20between%20the%20U.S.%20and%20Kuwait%2C%20ensuring%20a%20more%20secure%20and%20stable%20region.%3Cp%3EU.S.%20Air%20Force%20photo%20by%20Staff%20Sgt.%20Tylin%20Rust%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20high%20thrust-to-weight%20ratio%20also%20allows%20the%20F-15E%20Strike%20Eagle%20to%20execute%20tight%20turns%20without%20sacrificing%20speed.%20It%20has%20two%20Pratt%20%26amp%3B%20Whitney%20F100%20engines%2C%20each%20producing%20over%2023%2C000%20pounds%20of%20thrust.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EAnother%20distinguishing%20capability%20is%20the%20plane's%20head-up%20display%2C%20which%20projects%20flight%20and%20tactical%20information%20directly%20on%20the%20windscreen.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20head-up%20display%20on%20a%20C-17%20Globemaster%20III.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b1b33d4d65ec517529d75f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222288%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20U.S.%20Air%20Force%20C-17%20Globemaster%20III%20aircraft%2C%20operated%20by%20the%20204th%20Airlift%20Squadron%2C%20Hawaii%20Air%20National%20Guard%2C%20is%20captured%20through%20the%20head-up%20display%20of%20another%20C-17%20during%20a%20training%20sortie%20Dec.%201%2C%202025%2C%20off%20the%20coast%20of%20Hawaii.The%20204th%20Airlift%20Squadron%20operates%20under%20the%20Total%20Force%20Initiative%2C%20with%20aircraft%20crewed%20and%20maintained%20jointly%20by%20Hawaii%20Air%20National%20Guard%20Airmen%20of%20the%20154th%20Wing%20and%20active-duty%20Airmen%20of%20the%2015th%20Wing.%3Cp%3EU.S.%20Air%20National%20Guard%20photo%20by%20Tech.%20Sgt.%20John%20Linzmeier%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPilots%20can%20track%20and%20attack%20targets%2C%20check%20the%20status%20of%20weapons%2C%20and%20see%20other%20tactical%20and%20flight%20information%20without%20taking%20their%20eyes%20off%20the%20windscreen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20fighter%20jet%20also%20includes%20a%20low-altitude%20navigation%20and%20targeting%20infrared%20for%20night%20(LANTIRN)%20system.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222964%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20underside%20of%20an%20F-15E%20Strike%20Eagle.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b1b71ba7a4f9df67ba2c6d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222371%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20U.S.%20Air%20Force%20F-15E%20Strike%20Eagle%20assigned%20to%20the%20492nd%20Fighter%20Squadron%20takes%20off%20from%20Royal%20Air%20Force%20Lakenheath%2C%20England%2C%20June%2027%2C%202023.%20F-15%20training%20sorties%20are%20conducted%20by%2048th%20Fighter%20Wing%20members%20to%20ensure%20they%20stay%20prepared%20and%20efficient%20to%20provide%20a%20strategic%20force%20whenever%20they%20are%20called%20upon%20for%20a%20mission.%20(U.S.%20Air%20Force%20Photo%20by%20Airman%201st%20Class%20Olivia%20Gibson)%3Cp%3EU.S.%20Air%20Force%20Photo%20by%20Airman%201st%20Class%20Olivia%20Gibson%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20LANTIRN%20system%20allows%20the%20planes%20to%20fly%20in%20any%20weather%20and%20attack%20ground%20targets%20at%20low%20altitudes.%20The%20system%20consists%20of%20two%20pods%2C%20a%20navigation%20pod%20and%20a%20targeting%20pod%2C%20mounted%20under%20the%20plane.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EF-15E%20Strike%20Eagles%20can%20carry%20both%20nuclear%20and%20conventional%20weapons.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Loading%20an%20AIM-120%20missile%20onto%20an%20F-15E%20Strike%20Eagle%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b2cc8ca96e437d6eb831b9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EU.S.%20Air%20Force%20Staff%20Sgt.%20Sean%20Policarpio%20and%20Senior%20Airman%20Angelo%20Val%2C%20389th%20Fighter%20Generation%20Squadron%20load%20crew%20members%2C%20load%20an%20AIM-120%20missile%20onto%20an%20F-15E%20Strike%20Eagle%20aircraft%20at%20Mountain%20Home%20Air%20Force%20Base%2C%20Idaho%2C%20Oct.%2024%2C%202025.%20Weapons%20load%20crews%20work%20together%20to%20ensure%20munitions%20are%20safely%20loaded%20and%20mission%20ready%20for%20F-15E%20Strike%20Eagle%20operations.%3Cp%3EAirman%201st%20Class%20Donovin%20Watson%2F366th%20Fighter%20Wing%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20armament%20includes%20an%20internally%20mounted%2020-millimeter%20gun%20with%20500%20rounds%20of%20ammunition%2C%20AIM-9%20Sidewinder%20missiles%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpentagon-award-air-to-air-missiles-surging-demand-thin-stockpiles-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAIM-120%20AMRAAMs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20acronym%20for%20the%20radar-guided%20Advanced%20Medium-Range%20Air-to