langerie%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20tiny%20bakery%20tucked%20between%20a%20delicatessen%20and%20a%20nail%20salon%20on%20Los%20Angeles'%20iconic%20Wilshire%20Boulevard.%20Five%20days%20a%20week%2C%20her%20alarm%20goes%20off%20at%2012%3A48%20a.m.%2C%20giving%20her%20just%20enough%20time%20to%20get%20out%20of%20bed%2C%20walk%20the%2010%20blocks%20to%20the%20shop%2C%20and%20start%20shaping%20croissants%20by%201%20a.m.%20She%20relieves%20her%2023-year-old%20daughter%2C%20who%20works%20the%205%20p.m.%20to%201%20a.m.%20night%20shift.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20early%20hours%20aren't%20for%20show.%20They're%20key%20to%20good%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20foot%20traffic%20happens%20between%208%20a.m.%2C%20when%20her%20bakery%20opens%2C%20and%2010%3A30%20a.m.%2C%20she%20explained%3A%20%26quot%3BIf%20we%20don't%20have%20enough%20things%20to%20sell%20because%20we%20shaped%20too%20late%20or%20they%20went%20into%20the%20proofer%20too%20late%2C%20then%20we%20lose%20money.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%201%20a.m.%20to%203%20a.m.%2C%20she%20works%20alone%20in%20the%20kitchen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20my%20favorite%20time%20of%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20mother%20of%20three%2C%20%26quot%3Bbecause%20I%20just%20listen%20to%20true-crime%20podcasts.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider's%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftinyurl.com%2Fgoing-for-growth%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoing%20for%20Growth%3C%2Fa%3E%20series%20explores%20how%20small-business%20owners%20are%20scaling%20their%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%203%20a.m.%2C%20a%20second%20baker%20arrives%2C%20followed%20by%20three%20more%2C%20staggered%20at%204%20a.m.%2C%205%20a.m.%2C%20and%206%20a.m.%20Front%20of%20house%20clocks%20in%20at%207%20a.m.%2C%20and%20the%20doors%20open%20an%20hour%20later.%20Regulars%20often%20line%20up%20well%20before%20then%20to%20secure%20their%20favorite%20pastries%2C%20including%20the%20most%20popular%20item%3A%20the%20plain%20croissant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Fridays%2C%20she%20typically%20works%20a%20half-day%20and%20focuses%20on%20business%20development.%20The%20Friday%20we%20chat%20is%20different.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20exterior%20of%20Petitgrain%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b46004a7a4f9df67ba528b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%2210000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPetitgrain%20Boulangerie%2C%20situated%20on%20Wilshire%20Boulevard%2C%20opened%20in%20May%202024.%3Cp%3EShelby%20Moore%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20week%2C%20I'm%20short-staffed%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20me%2C%20stepping%20out%20of%20the%20kitchen%20to%20take%20the%20call.%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20a%20nice%2C%20healthy%2045%20minutes%20ahead%20of%20me.%20I'm%20just%20waiting%20for%20things%20to%20rise%20in%20the%20proofer.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDe%20Lutz%20was%20born%20in%20Paris%20and%20moved%20with%20her%20family%20to%20Washington%2C%20D.C.%2C%20when%20she%20was%20eight.%20Summers%20were%20spent%20selling%20ice%20cream%20and%20washing%20dishes%20at%20the%20inn%20and%20restaurant%20her%20grandparents%20owned%20in%20the%20south%20of%20France.%20%26quot%3BMy%20parents%20would%20just%20drop%20us%20off%20for%20the%20summer%20and%20be%20like%2C%20'Work%20for%20tips%2C'%26quot%3B%20she%20recalled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20studied%20film%20and%20anthropology%20at%20Syracuse%20University%2C%20then%20moved%20to%20Los%20Angeles%20with%20plans%20to%20make%20documentaries.%20She%20tried%20the%20corporate%20route%20first%2C%20taking%20an%20executive%20assistant%20job%20at%20Fox%2C%20but%20it%20didn't%20last.%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20couldn't%20find%20my%20footing%20until%20I%20went%20back%20into%20food%20in%20my%20early%2020s%20and%20was%20like%2C%20'Oh%2C%20this%20is%20what%20feels%20normal%2C'%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BChaos%20feels%20normal.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Clemence%20prepping%20baked%20goods%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b45f27a7a4f9df67ba526f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%228000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDe%20Lutz%20starts%20prepping%20croissants%20at%201%20a.m.%20every%20morning%20the%20bakery%20is%20open.%3Cp%3EShelby%20Moore%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dd85efd5-3c9e-465b-be40-6724790743f1%5C%22%3ETurning%20a%20cubicle%20cookie%20side%20hustle%20into%20a%20career%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20a%20desk%20job%20wasn't%20a%20great%20fit%20for%20de%20Lutz%2C%20it%20led%20to%20a%20side%20hustle%20that%20would%20change%20the%20course%20of%20her%20career.%20She'd%20collect%20cookie%20orders%20from%20coworkers%20throughout%20the%20week%20and%20deliver%20her%20handmade%20creations%20on%20Fridays.%20Her%20cubicle%20cookie%20business%20eventually%20landed%20a%20spot%20on%20KCRW's%20%26quot%3BGood%20Food%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20appearance%20she%20says%20%26quot%3Bchanged%20my%20life.%26quot%3B%20She%20quit%20her%20job%2C%20rented%20a%20commercial%20kitchen%2C%20and%20began%20working%20as%20a%20ghost%20pastry%20chef%20for%20restaurants.%20Baking%20evolved%20into%20teaching%20and%20consulting.%20For%20years%2C%20she%20helped%20other%20bakeries%20build%20menus%20and%20streamline%20systems%2C%20work%20that%20also%20served%20as%20real-time%20education%20on%20what%20it%20takes%20to%20succeed%20in%20the%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20opportunity%20to%20run%20her%20own%20bakery%20fell%20into%20her%20lap%20%E2%80%94%20a%20friend%20she'd%20consulted%20for%20called%20her%20up%20and%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BHey%2C%20I'm%20retiring%2C%20do%20you%20want%20my%20space%3F%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20she%20jumped.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETaking%20over%20an%20existing%20kitchen%20space%20in%20LA%20typically%20comes%20with%20expensive%20delays%20and%20red%20tape.%20In%20Los%20Angeles%20County%2C%20she%20explained%2C%20commercial%20kitchens%20that%20sit%20empty%20for%2090%20days%20or%20more%20can%20trigger%20a%20permit%20reset.%20So%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhen%20you%20find%20an%20owner%20who%20is%20willing%20to%20work%20with%20you%20and%20close%20the%20day%20before%20you%20want%20to%20open%20and%20just%20kind%20of%20negotiate%20key%20money%20for%20buying%20out%20the%20equipment%2C%20you%20can%20never%20pass%20that%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20has%20lived%20lean%2C%20she%20said%2C%20with%20no%20credit%20card%20debt%20or%20loans%2C%20so%20the%20risk%20of%20opening%20felt%20manageable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20values%20I%20grew%20up%20with%20have%20very%20little%20to%20do%20with%20money.%20In%20France%2C%20it's%20not%20customary%20to%20value%20money%20or%20wealth.%20It's%20really%20valuing%20being%20a%20tradesperson%2C%20being%20an%20expert%20in%20your%20field%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BTaking%20risks%20was%20always%20easy%20because%20I%20had%20nothing%20to%20lose.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20baker%20arranges%20croissants%20on%20a%20tray.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b45d6a4d65ec517529fd8a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%2210000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20bakers%20at%20Petitgrain%20shape%20hundreds%20of%20croissants%20by%20hand%20a%20day.%3Cp%3EShelby%20Moore%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220e0ba3bb-d115-4729-ba86-f4218996316f%5C%22%3EOpening%20day%3A%20Selling%20300%20croissants%20in%201%20hour%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPetitgrain%20opened%20in%20May%202024.%20From%20the%20start%2C%20demand%20outpaced%20production.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpening%20day%2C%20she%20made%20about%20300%20croissants.%20They%20didn't%20last%20more%20than%20an%20hour.%20On%20day%20two%2C%20she%20about%20doubled%20the%20number%20and%20sold%20out%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20opening%2C%20the%20bakery%20has%20drawn%20steady%20crowds%20from%20Wednesday%20through%20Sunday%2C%20the%20days%20it's%20open.%20Today%2C%20the%20operation%20is%20close%20to%20its%20ceiling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20pretty%20maxed%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20Her%20870-square-foot%20kitchen%2C%20equipped%20with%20one%20double-stack%20oven%20and%20one%20small%20proofer%2C%20produces%2032%20%26quot%3Bbooks%26quot%3B%20of%20croissants%20a%20day.%20A%20book%20yields%20roughly%2024%20to%2030%20croissants%2C%20putting%20the%20daily%20volume%20at%20700%20to%20900.%20Though%20the%20croissant%20is%20the%20top%20seller%2C%20she%20offers%20a%20variety%20of%20other%20pastries%2C%20including%20cinnamon%2C%20cardamom%2C%20and%20sausage%20rolls%2C%20as%20well%20as%20cookies%2C%20quiche%2C%20and%20scones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20business%20worked%20from%20the%20get-go%20because%20she%20understood%20her%20baseline%20costs%20and%20built%20for%20sustainability.%20It%20helped%20that%20her%20landlord%20was%20committed%20to%20renting%20to%20small%20businesses%20at%20below-market%20rent%2C%20she%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BRent%20is%20%244%2C100%20a%20month%2C%20and%20we%20knew%20how%20much%20we%20needed%20to%20make%20to%20make%20rent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20on%2C%20she%20kept%20a%20second%20job%20teaching%20baking%20classes%2C%20but%20within%20a%20couple%20of%20months%20of%20opening%2C%20she%20sold%20her%20share%20of%20the%20cooking%20school%20to%20focus%20fully%20on%20Petitgrain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDe%20Lutz%20said%20Petitgrain's%20average%20monthly%20sales%20have%20climbed%20about%20131%25%20from%202024%2C%20when%20she%20first%20opened%2C%20as%20the%20team%20slowly%20increased%20production.%20Small%20upgrades%2C%20such%20as%20undercounter%20freezers%2C%20have%20helped%20drive%20another%2020%25%20in%20growth%20over%20the%20last%20few%20months%2C%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Shelby%20preps%20her%20baked%20goods%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b46199a7a4f9df67ba52c1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%226300%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDe%20Lutz%20sources%20nearly%20every%20ingredient%20from%20farms%20around%20LA.%3Cp%3EShelby%20Moore%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2205b08832-ccc8-49df-ade5-27b356bfd803%5C%22%3EHer%20secret%20sauce%3A%20Social%20capital%20and%20'radical%20hospitality'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20ripped%20open%20one%20of%20her%20flaky%20masterpieces%20myself%2C%20it's%20hard%20to%20agree%20with%20de%20Lutz%20when%20she%20claims%20her%20croissants%20are%20%26quot%3Boverhyped.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20kidding%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20when%20I%20chuckled.%20%26quot%3BI%20wake%20up%20every%20morning%20at%2012%3A48%20a.m.%2C%20and%20my%20first%20thought%20is%3A%20'How%20can%20I%20live%20up%20to%20this%20hype%3F'%20It's%20a%20lot%20of%20expectations%2C%20but%20it's%20sort%20of%20what%20drives%20you%20to%20be%20excellent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20big%20part%20of%20her%20immediate%20success%2C%20she%20believes%2C%20was%20timing.%20When%20Petitgrain%20opened%2C%20interest%20in%20croissants%20surged%20across%20Los%20Angeles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEverybody%20all%20of%20a%20sudden%20wanted%20to%20write%20about%20croissants%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20just%20really%20lucky%20timing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELess%20visible%2C%20and%20perhaps%20more%20impactful%20than%20trends%2C%20however%2C%20were%20the%20relationships%20she'd%20built%20from%20being%20in%20the%20food%20and%20hospitality%20community%20for%20so%20long.%20Social%20capital%2C%20she%20said%2C%20is%20%26quot%3Bthe%20most%20important%20part%20of%20my%20story.%26quot%3B%20While%20it's%20hard%20to%20quantify%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20that%20has%20the%20biggest%20return.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20hiring%20model%20and%20teambuilding%20strategies%20are%20unique.%20At%20Petitgrain%2C%20she%20practices%20what%20she%20calls%20%26quot%3Bboth-of-house%26quot%3B%20training%3A%20everyone%20in%20back%20of%20house%20learns%20front%20of%20house%2C%20and%20everyone%20in%20front%20of%20house%20works%20at%20least%20one%20back-of-house%20shift%20weekly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Clemence%20and%20an%20employee%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b45e19a96e437d6eb84c1c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%228000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDe%20Lutz%20has%20a%20team%20of%2013%20bakers%20and%20baristas.%3Cp%3EShelby%20Moore%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20way%2C%20%26quot%3Beveryone%20understands%20the%20product%20better%20and%20has%20respect%20for%20their%20team%20members%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20She%20also%20rejects%20a%20traditional%20hierarchy%20and%20instead%20aims%20for%20shared%20accountability%2C%20anchored%20in%20wages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20business%20model%20is%20based%20on%20generous%20hospitality%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BEverybody%20needs%20to%20earn%20a%20living%20wage%2C%20not%20like%20%2420%20an%20hour.%20Everyone%20here%2C%20with%20tips%2C%20is%20making%20at%20minimum%20%2430%20an%20hour.%20I%20don't%20want%20anyone%20to%20have%20to%20work%20a%20second%20job.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20make%20that%20work%2C%20she%20runs%20a%20tip%20pool%2C%20and%20she%20protects%20it.%20She%20refuses%20to%20hire%20ahead%20of%20revenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBecause%20the%20tip%20pool%20is%20such%20an%20important%20part%20of%20everybody's%20paycheck%2C%20I'm%20really%20cautious%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20cannot%20bring%20in%20a%20new%20team%20member%20until%20we%20grow%20sales%20between%206%20and%208%25%20at%20a%20time%20because%2C%20if%20I%20add%20an%20extra%20person%20before%20revenue%20grows%2C%20everybody's%20tip%20pool%20gets%20diluted.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20early%202026%2C%20she%20has%20a%20team%20of%2013%20bakers%20and%20baristas.%20When%20she%20does%20hire%2C%20credentials%20aren't%20her%20priority.%20She's%20looking%20for%20kindness%2C%20hustle%2C%20and%20curiosity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20care%20if%20you%20went%20to%20culinary%20school.%20I%20don't%20care%20if%20you%20worked%20at%20a%20Michelin-star%20restaurant%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BHonestly%2C%20it's%20not%20hard%20to%20make%20a%20croissant.%20It%20really%20isn't.%20But%20if%20you%20are%20curious%2C%20if%20you%20are%20humble%2C%20if%20you%20work%20hard%2C%20you'll%20figure%20it%20out.%20And%2099%25%20of%20the%20time%2C%20that%20yields%20a%20really%20great%20team.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnderneath%20all%20of%20it%20is%20what%20she%20calls%20her%20core%20belief%20system%3A%20radical%20generosity%2C%20expressed%20through%20radical%20hospitality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20never%20a%20time%20when%20I%20have%20been%20radically%20generous%20and%20regretted%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-origin-of-petitgrain-boulangerie-top-bakery-los-angeles-california-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1773678203000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b45be2a96e437d6eb84bbd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-origin-of-petitgrain-boulangerie-top-bakery-los-angeles-california-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Behind%20Petitgrain%20Boulangerie%2C%20one%20of%20the%20most%20popular%20bakeries%20in%20LA%2C%20is%20Cl%C3%A9mence%20de%20Lutz%2C%20whose%20work%20day%20begins%20in%20the%20kitchen%20at%201%20a.m.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kelkins%40businessinsider.com%20(Kathleen%20Elkins)%22%2C%22engageme